reviews.title: Disappointment made up for
reviews.text:
The service of this establishment is highly dependent on the mood of some staff members. In case of crowds, most of the servants are not stress resistant. Then it is often not even possible to order a drink at the bar. 
I was told to return to my table and wait for the servant.
Because there was no free table to find, I had to wait for a chair in a small corner with a dry throat. However, a rock is the Senior servant 'Femmie'; She immediately offered me a nice table on the terrace, and immediately provided me with a drink. She is also often single-handedly able to keep things running and does not allow herself to be fooled. She is very customer-oriented and very friendly. If the world were just Femmies we would be living in a utopia.

tips.body: Zorg dat je geholpen wordt door het ervaren personeel (Femmie)

reviews.title: Comfortable cafe/restaurant with view in harbor
reviews.text: Authentic Dutch cafe/bar inside and comfortable seating on terrace outside. Limited items on menu, but taste was very good, especially the ‘mustard soup’ of the day. Good service.

reviews.title: Great views and food
reviews.text: Lovely staff...food was generous indeed portion wise and very tasty...good background music going down.

reviews.title: Great bar staff
reviews.text: Spent a couple of weeks working at shipyard, went to this bar nearly every night after work for a couple of drinks really friendly bar staff, always happy to have a chat with us, making us feel welcome as we were from UK , great bar

tripContent.title: Head to Fort Myers for amazing outdoor adventures
tripContent.description: Seeking adventure on your next vacation? Head to the greater Fort Myers area, where action-packed onshore and offshore activities are yours to enjoy year-round. Water sports, nature parks and wildlife excursions are just some of the highlights on this itinerary that is all about having fun in the sun.

articleContent.title: Start here: these hotels will inspire your entire trip

seoInfo.metaDescription: When choosing a stay for your long-awaited vacation, the usual checklist comes to mind: good location, comfy room, and, if you’re lucky, a pool. But if the goal of your getaway is to explore someplace new, shouldn’t you expect cultural experiences and local flavor from your hotel, too?

articleContent.title: How to eat your way through Greenville, SC

seoInfo.metaDescription: For those who plan their meals before booking a plane ticket, listen up: There is a place where you can immerse yourself in the dining cultures of 34 countries across five continents without leaving a single city limit. Greenville, South Carolina is much more than a restaurant hub—it has enough festivals, food tours, and dinner views to fuel a lifetime of trips. All of this in mind, it’s no wonder the region will be featured on Season 23 of Bravo’s Top Chef, and host the inaugural Michelin Guide American South Ceremony.

They say two is better than one—and in Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo, that couldn’t be more true. Ixtapa is modern and vibrant, with luxury resorts, breathtaking views, and settings surrounded by lush tropical nature. Zihuatanejo, a Pueblo Mágico, offers cobblestone streets, deep-rooted traditions, and a laid-back coastal vibe. Together, they deliver a travel experience that’s as diverse as it is authentic—earning Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo its place among Mexico’s top beach destinations.

articleContent.title: Discover the spirited soul of Bourbon City

seoInfo.metaDescription: Raise a glass to the charm of Louisville, Kentucky—a town with a rich history and a smooth bourbon scene, where each sip serves up a story of tradition and innovation. With iconic distilleries, exciting restaurants, and warm southern hospitality, Louisville’s authentic spirit is proof that the heart and soul of Bourbon City has aged to perfection.
